Key Match Events: The game went into overtime as the Warriors and Rockets tied 119-119 at the end of the fourth quarter.
Buddy Hield and Jonathan Kuminga came off the bench to prop up 27 and 23 points respectively in overtime.
The Warriors were helped by buckets from Kuminga and Anderson in overtime as they put some distance between the two teams.
Post-Match Reflections: The win sees the Warriors improve to 5-1, and they head to the Capital One Arena next to take on the Washington Wizards on Nov. 4.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Warriors stuck to their plans of getting Jonathan Kuminga off the bench again, with Moses Moody and Brandin Podziemski forming the backcourt.
Houston was slow off the blocks allowing the Warriors to prop up an 18-point lead in the first quarter.
The Rockets capitalized on the Warriors' 18 missed free throws and sputtering offense to force an overtime contest.
The Warriors lost the rebounding battle 49-47 and made just 64% of their shots from the charity stripe.
Others: The game was played at the Toyota Center on Saturday (Nov. 2).
The Warriors' win sees them open their five-game road stretch as they continue their run without superstar Steph Curry in the fold.
